<br>
I have not had a chance to meet you yet but it has been only <em>one</em> day since you joined the guild. Using words like BS and spam, which are rather inflammatory and subjective, may not go over well with your new guild members when you're talking about them.  I would suggest addressing specific topics if they bother you.<br>
<br>
This guild has been around for a year now and many of us have become good friends that go beyond getting hunting parties together.  Some of my best friends can no longer group with me because our levels are so varied, including Zandzack.  However, I still enjoy knowing what they're up to and I know I'm not the only one that feels this way.  I believe this kinsmanship is the foundation of our guild and is why we've stuck together.<br>
<br>
I suggest you get to know the people in your guild, perhaps you will begin to enjoy the chat as well.  On the other hand as I said, if there was some chat that was offensive, it should be addressed.<br>
<br>
Taansey<br>
