<br>
The reason for this?  Well, as Taan said, some of us are up in level, and rarely ever see our other guildmates.  I'm level 53, and the only people in the guild I've grouped with recently are Taan and Gal.  As for everyone else, the only way I can tell how they're doing ingame is through guildchat.  I love to hear about how great someone feels after slaying their first griffon, and I love telling the guild how irritated I get when a seafury cyclops resists half of my spells.  This guild is like a family to me.  I've been here from the start (in the form of too many characters to count), and ever since the beginning, the guild was family-oriented.  <br>
